1
00:00:38,180 --> 00:00:42,060
=The Hidden Truth=

2
00:00:42,060 --> 00:00:44,700
=Episode 1=

3
00:01:14,040 --> 00:01:14,880
You okay?

4
00:01:20,000 --> 00:01:20,860
It's fine, Master.

5
00:01:20,950 --> 00:01:22,510
The puppy just ran off on its own.

6
00:01:23,350 --> 00:01:24,200
It wasn't stolen.

7
00:01:24,230 --> 00:01:25,070
I've handled it.

8
00:01:28,560 --> 00:01:30,310
The department's clearing cold cases, right?

9
00:01:30,520 --> 00:01:31,650
Is that what it's about?

10
00:01:32,320 --> 00:01:33,500
The Nude Banquet Case 15 years ago.

11
00:01:33,520 --> 00:01:34,320
Time to reopen it?

12
00:01:36,790 --> 00:01:38,710
Why's it got nothing to do with me, Master?

13
00:01:39,280 --> 00:01:40,760
It's the oldest case we've sat on.

14
00:01:40,760 --> 00:01:41,980
Who wouldn't want to crack it?

15
00:01:42,350 --> 00:01:43,950
I'm a detective, Master.

16
00:01:43,950 --> 00:01:44,790
I can't...

17
00:01:44,950 --> 00:01:46,590
I can't spend my days chasing dogs.

18
00:01:46,590 --> 00:01:47,790
Everyone's got a dream, right?

19
00:02:00,760 --> 00:02:02,510
Give me back Jinbao.

20
00:02:02,510 --> 00:02:03,480
(Qingcheng Public Security Bureau)
Give me back Jinbao.

21
00:02:03,480 --> 00:02:04,320
Give me back Jinbao.

22
00:02:04,340 --> 00:02:05,260
Jinbao is 5 months old.

23
00:02:05,280 --> 00:02:06,280
Everyone, calm down.

24
00:02:06,480 --> 00:02:07,480
Give me back Jinbao.

25
00:02:07,480 --> 00:02:08,680
Jinbao is 5 months old.

26
00:02:08,680 --> 00:02:09,710
Give me back Jinbao.

27
00:02:09,710 --> 00:02:11,910
Everyone, calm down, please. Calm down.

28
00:02:11,910 --> 00:02:14,520
Seriously, when are you going
to solve this case?

29
00:02:14,750 --> 00:02:17,120
My baby ate the poisoned sausage.

30
00:02:17,120 --> 00:02:18,870
It's still lying in the hospital.

31
00:02:19,310 --> 00:02:21,240
Who's going to cover all these expenses?

32
00:02:21,680 --> 00:02:22,750
Please don't worry.

33
00:02:22,750 --> 00:02:24,680
We're working on a solution as we speak.

34
00:02:25,150 --> 00:02:26,600
What exactly have you solved so far?

35
00:02:26,710 --> 00:02:27,590
All you do is talk.

36
00:02:27,910 --> 00:02:29,430
We need you to catch the culprit.

37
00:02:29,590 --> 00:02:31,360
Otherwise, none of us will feel safe.

38
00:02:31,430 --> 00:02:32,590
Exactly, not safe at all.

39
00:02:32,590 --> 00:02:33,430
Not safe.

40
00:02:33,560 --> 00:02:35,710
We've already
worked out the plan and measures.

41
00:02:35,840 --> 00:02:37,280
We'll catch the offenders soon.

42
00:02:37,430 --> 00:02:38,710
Please don't worry, okay?

43
00:02:38,830 --> 00:02:39,750
Do the job if you can.

44
00:02:39,960 --> 00:02:40,810
If you can't,

45
00:02:40,910 --> 00:02:42,360
might as well shut the station down.

46
00:02:42,630 --> 00:02:44,960
Yeah, shut it down.

47
00:02:44,990 --> 00:02:46,030
If there's no explanation,

48
00:02:46,030 --> 00:02:47,240
we're not leaving.

49
00:02:47,240 --> 00:02:49,120
That's right. We're not leaving.

50
00:02:49,120 --> 00:02:50,270
- Right.
- Tang Tang's back.

51
00:02:50,680 --> 00:02:52,400
Were you swimming or catching dogs?

52
00:02:54,360 --> 00:02:55,750
You think being a detective is easy?

53
00:02:55,800 --> 00:02:57,030
Even lost dogs are our job now.

54
00:02:57,030 --> 00:02:57,910
What a joke.

55
00:02:59,190 --> 00:03:00,960
If you can't be civil, don't say anything.

56
00:03:01,190 --> 00:03:02,840
Can't you see what's going on out there?

57
00:03:06,680 --> 00:03:10,360
Excuse me, coming through.

58
00:03:14,220 --> 00:03:15,080
Why are you so wet?

59
00:03:15,430 --> 00:03:16,270
Don't mention it.

60
00:03:23,240 --> 00:03:24,080
Please sit down.

61
00:03:27,590 --> 00:03:28,430
Comrades,

62
00:03:28,960 --> 00:03:30,870
I'm sure you've already

63
00:03:31,310 --> 00:03:34,150
heard about our meeting today.

64
00:03:34,800 --> 00:03:36,310
The main topic

65
00:03:36,710 --> 00:03:38,280
is clearing old unresolved cases.

66
00:03:39,150 --> 00:03:40,150
Many of these cases,

67
00:03:40,520 --> 00:03:42,710
due to investigative limitations at the time,

68
00:03:43,270 --> 00:03:44,480
ran into serious difficulties.

69
00:03:45,400 --> 00:03:46,960
But cold cases

70
00:03:47,430 --> 00:03:49,590
shouldn't just sit in our file cabinets.

71
00:03:50,000 --> 00:03:51,710
They should weigh on the minds of us.

72
00:03:53,440 --> 00:03:54,870
The provincial department's launched

73
00:03:54,910 --> 00:03:56,590
a campaign to crack cold cases.

74
00:03:57,030 --> 00:03:59,150
Our bureau must respond actively

75
00:03:59,350 --> 00:04:00,440
and carry out the operation.

76
00:04:00,910 --> 00:04:01,800
The first case

77
00:04:02,080 --> 00:04:03,630
to be tackled

78
00:04:04,180 --> 00:04:05,190
is the Nude Banquet Case.

79
00:04:06,080 --> 00:04:07,960
Everyone's got the case file, right?

80
00:04:14,280 --> 00:04:15,120
Back then,

81
00:04:15,470 --> 00:04:19,000
the disappearance of businessman Liu Xijun

82
00:04:19,140 --> 00:04:20,580
led us to uncover a nude banquet.

83
00:04:20,920 --> 00:04:23,510
Most of the victims were minors.

84
00:04:24,310 --> 00:04:25,190
The crime was heinous,

85
00:04:25,680 --> 00:04:28,270
with severe social impact and public outcry.

86
00:04:29,680 --> 00:04:32,680
Several businessmen involved were arrested,

87
00:04:33,270 --> 00:04:35,390
along with welfare home staff

88
00:04:35,510 --> 00:04:37,720
who colluded with the ring,

89
00:04:37,800 --> 00:04:40,310
luring and trafficking orphans.

90
00:04:41,070 --> 00:04:43,070
There are three obstacles in this case.

91
00:04:43,730 --> 00:04:44,610
First,

92
00:04:44,630 --> 00:04:45,720
according to the confessions

93
00:04:46,160 --> 00:04:47,680
of the welfare home social worker,

94
00:04:48,160 --> 00:04:50,920
the ringleader, Bai Qiming, is dead.

95
00:04:51,390 --> 00:04:53,160
But the cause of his death is unknown.

96
00:04:53,950 --> 00:04:54,790
Second,

97
00:04:55,000 --> 00:04:56,600
as stated by the arrested businessmen,

98
00:04:56,920 --> 00:04:58,270
they were all kept blindfolded

99
00:04:58,460 --> 00:04:59,700
when taken to the banquet site.

100
00:05:00,270 --> 00:05:01,110
As a result,

101
00:05:01,240 --> 00:05:02,870
no one can identify

102
00:05:03,190 --> 00:05:04,950
the exact location of the banquet.

103
00:05:06,310 --> 00:05:07,150
Third,

104
00:05:07,330 --> 00:05:08,590
after Liu Xijun disappeared,

105
00:05:08,920 --> 00:05:10,430
he was presumed dead,

106
00:05:10,830 --> 00:05:13,120
but his body has never been found.

107
00:05:14,190 --> 00:05:16,480
These three issues were never resolved,

108
00:05:17,160 --> 00:05:18,480
and the investigation

109
00:05:18,720 --> 00:05:20,830
was brought to a standstill.

110
00:05:27,950 --> 00:05:28,790
Master.

111
00:05:30,510 --> 00:05:31,350
Zhao.

112
00:05:32,000 --> 00:05:34,160
You were one of the detectives

113
00:05:34,160 --> 00:05:35,390
who worked this case back then.

114
00:05:35,870 --> 00:05:37,270
Fifteen years have passed,

115
00:05:37,560 --> 00:05:39,390
but you still need that drive.

116
00:05:41,000 --> 00:05:41,840
Chief,

117
00:05:41,920 --> 00:05:44,040
I may be close to retirement,

118
00:05:44,920 --> 00:05:45,760
but my drive

119
00:05:46,120 --> 00:05:47,160
is definitely still there.

120
00:05:48,510 --> 00:05:49,350
However,

121
00:05:49,720 --> 00:05:51,310
the Dog Theft Case we're handling now

122
00:05:51,830 --> 00:05:53,870
is causing a huge stir in the community.

123
00:05:54,080 --> 00:05:54,920
It's urgent.

124
00:05:54,920 --> 00:05:55,760
Sir.

125
00:05:57,050 --> 00:05:58,410
I volunteer to take this case.

126
00:05:58,550 --> 00:05:59,390
I'll sign a pledge.

127
00:05:59,430 --> 00:06:00,520
I guarantee I'll solve it.

128
00:06:00,830 --> 00:06:01,670
Sit down.

129
00:06:02,120 --> 00:06:03,600
The Dog Theft Case isn't closed yet.

130
00:06:03,780 --> 00:06:05,030
Why are you making that pledge?

131
00:06:05,830 --> 00:06:06,670
Sit down.

132
00:06:14,650 --> 00:06:15,510
Master,

133
00:06:15,630 --> 00:06:17,240
the Chief practically named you just now.

134
00:06:17,260 --> 00:06:18,290
Why didn't you respond?

135
00:06:18,330 --> 00:06:19,730
Team One gets all the major cases.

136
00:06:19,800 --> 00:06:20,640
You jealous?

137
00:06:21,560 --> 00:06:22,800
I'm not jealous.

138
00:06:23,330 --> 00:06:24,680
I just want the Nude Banquet Case.

139
00:06:24,830 --> 00:06:26,830
You're just upset our team gets small cases.

140
00:06:29,000 --> 00:06:30,870
Don't bite off more than you can handle.

141
00:06:31,040 --> 00:06:32,750
You might trip yourself up chasing that.

142
00:06:33,040 --> 00:06:33,880
Master,

143
00:06:34,000 --> 00:06:36,120
how is that aiming too high?

144
00:06:36,270 --> 00:06:37,360
I want to work big cases.

145
00:06:37,360 --> 00:06:38,200
I'm a detective.

146
00:06:38,390 --> 00:06:40,190
I can't spend every day catching dogs.

147
00:06:40,360 --> 00:06:41,510
We finally land a major case,

148
00:06:41,680 --> 00:06:43,180
and you won't even fight for it.

149
00:06:43,210 --> 00:06:44,420
What do you expect me to do?

150
00:06:44,560 --> 00:06:46,510
Catching dogs doesn't change who we are.

151
00:06:47,360 --> 00:06:48,800
Look at the people outside.

152
00:06:49,000 --> 00:06:49,920
They're desperate.

153
00:06:50,580 --> 00:06:51,870
Aren't their concerns real too?

154
00:06:52,360 --> 00:06:54,390
So everything I just said means nothing?

155
00:06:54,950 --> 00:06:56,240
You're about to retire.

156
00:06:56,510 --> 00:06:58,270
I haven't even started yet.

157
00:06:58,480 --> 00:06:59,510
How are we the same?

158
00:07:00,390 --> 00:07:01,230
Captain Zhao.

159
00:07:02,040 --> 00:07:02,880
Something's happened.

160
00:07:03,000 --> 00:07:03,840
What is it?

161
00:07:06,020 --> 00:07:13,700
(Police)

162
00:07:22,180 --> 00:07:25,660
(Crime Scene Investigation)

163
00:07:44,510 --> 00:07:45,350
Captain Zhao.

164
00:07:46,680 --> 00:07:47,520
What do we have?

165
00:07:47,560 --> 00:07:48,720
Based on the body,

166
00:07:48,720 --> 00:07:50,390
time of death was about 4 to 5 days ago.

167
00:07:50,630 --> 00:07:51,920
No visible external injuries.

168
00:07:52,600 --> 00:07:54,480
The room is messy,

169
00:07:54,720 --> 00:07:56,160
but that appears to be how she lived.

170
00:07:56,360 --> 00:07:57,720
No signs of a struggle were found.

171
00:08:06,680 --> 00:08:08,830
We found that sausage in the victim's hand.

172
00:08:08,940 --> 00:08:09,790
As for what's in it,

173
00:08:09,800 --> 00:08:10,730
we need to take it back

174
00:08:10,750 --> 00:08:11,950
for further testing.

175
00:08:13,120 --> 00:08:13,960
She was holding it?

176
00:08:14,390 --> 00:08:15,230
Yes.

177
00:08:23,920 --> 00:08:24,760
Master,

178
00:08:25,660 --> 00:08:26,640
it's a poisoned sausage.

179
00:08:26,900 --> 00:08:28,070
Same method as the dog thief.

180
00:08:32,150 --> 00:08:34,240
Who found the scene first?

181
00:08:34,870 --> 00:08:36,200
That old lady Liu Yan

182
00:08:36,200 --> 00:08:38,080
usually dug through trash bins for bottles.

183
00:08:38,260 --> 00:08:39,540
A smell in her place is normal.

184
00:08:39,840 --> 00:08:41,720
But the neighbors on the same floor

185
00:08:41,720 --> 00:08:43,130
said the odor was overwhelming.

186
00:08:43,160 --> 00:08:44,180
So they asked management

187
00:08:44,240 --> 00:08:45,320
to check it out.

188
00:08:45,560 --> 00:08:46,780
I came over and took a whiff.

189
00:08:47,030 --> 00:08:48,150
It really didn't smell right.

190
00:08:48,510 --> 00:08:49,720
I knocked but no one answered.

191
00:08:49,760 --> 00:08:51,340
So I used the spare key to open the door.

192
00:08:51,790 --> 00:08:52,840
And then I saw her.

193
00:08:53,750 --> 00:08:55,270
What were Liu Yan's daily habits like?

194
00:08:55,790 --> 00:08:57,080
Anyone she had contact with?

195
00:08:57,870 --> 00:08:58,870
That I really don't know.

196
00:08:59,080 --> 00:09:00,720
She didn't associate with anyone.

197
00:09:01,000 --> 00:09:01,840
Always alone.

198
00:09:02,030 --> 00:09:03,630
What about her daughter or any family?

199
00:09:03,630 --> 00:09:05,550
She moved here alone about 5 or 6 years ago.

200
00:09:06,030 --> 00:09:08,200
I heard she did some time before.

201
00:09:08,630 --> 00:09:10,510
Never seen anyone visit her place.

202
00:09:11,200 --> 00:09:12,080
Most of the time,

203
00:09:12,360 --> 00:09:13,270
she was all by herself,

204
00:09:13,270 --> 00:09:15,870
living off collecting bottles, very stingy.

205
00:09:18,080 --> 00:09:20,480
Has she had conflicts with anyone?

206
00:09:20,790 --> 00:09:21,840
Plenty.

207
00:09:22,600 --> 00:09:23,550
Over a single bottle,

208
00:09:24,120 --> 00:09:25,360
she'd go to any lengths.

209
00:09:29,000 --> 00:09:30,360
Did she do all that alone?

210
00:09:31,840 --> 00:09:32,870
She had a dog.

211
00:09:33,150 --> 00:09:34,000
Filthy thing.

212
00:09:34,440 --> 00:09:35,480
Guess it ran off hungry.

213
00:09:37,120 --> 00:09:38,240
Any other habits she has?

214
00:09:39,670 --> 00:09:40,840
Let me think.

215
00:09:41,790 --> 00:09:43,030
She went every day

216
00:09:43,030 --> 00:09:44,790
to Beifang Farmers' Market to buy veggies.

217
00:09:44,910 --> 00:09:46,030
But these past two weeks,

218
00:09:46,480 --> 00:09:47,870
she hardly went at all.

219
00:09:51,270 --> 00:09:54,000
Liu Yan had a routine of buying veggies.

220
00:09:54,050 --> 00:09:55,800
Half a month ago, she suddenly stopped going.

221
00:09:56,150 --> 00:09:57,120
That's suspicious.

222
00:09:58,840 --> 00:09:59,960
When we get to the market,

223
00:10:00,040 --> 00:10:01,480
we'll do a quick round of interviews,

224
00:10:01,870 --> 00:10:03,030
see if we get any leads.

225
00:10:03,440 --> 00:10:04,510
Liu Yan's death

226
00:10:04,510 --> 00:10:06,550
is definitely connected to the dog thief.

227
00:10:07,200 --> 00:10:08,320
The sausages are the same.

228
00:10:08,550 --> 00:10:09,750
Wait for the forensic results.

229
00:10:10,190 --> 00:10:11,510
The poison used will be the same.

230
00:10:12,870 --> 00:10:14,520
What, your eyes are a microscope now?

231
00:10:14,610 --> 00:10:16,240
One look and you can tell the ingredients?

232
00:10:16,630 --> 00:10:18,200
Guess we don't need to interview anyone.

233
00:10:19,480 --> 00:10:20,320
Don't doubt it.

234
00:10:20,910 --> 00:10:21,750
We'll see.

235
00:10:48,390 --> 00:10:49,230
Over there.

236
00:10:51,870 --> 00:10:52,710
Sir.

237
00:10:54,640 --> 00:10:55,630
I had two questions.

238
00:10:58,600 --> 00:10:59,530
Have you seen her?

239
00:11:00,480 --> 00:11:01,320
Her?

240
00:11:01,670 --> 00:11:03,120
She's a regular at this market.

241
00:11:03,440 --> 00:11:05,000
She hasn't come much lately.

242
00:11:05,510 --> 00:11:06,960
Seems like she suddenly had money

243
00:11:07,750 --> 00:11:09,910
and started eating at that wonton shop.

244
00:11:12,790 --> 00:11:14,120
Suddenly had money?

245
00:11:17,600 --> 00:11:18,990
- Thank you.
- Sure, sure.

246
00:11:19,200 --> 00:11:20,050
Let go.

247
00:11:20,120 --> 00:11:21,360
That dog's hers.

248
00:11:21,480 --> 00:11:22,440
We've got proof.

249
00:11:22,440 --> 00:11:23,290
Proof my foot.

250
00:11:23,290 --> 00:11:24,270
You are working together.

251
00:11:24,370 --> 00:11:25,890
Can't pay, so you're stealing the dog?

252
00:11:25,960 --> 00:11:27,240
Let go. Let go.

253
00:11:27,670 --> 00:11:29,480
The girls don't look shady.

254
00:11:29,480 --> 00:11:31,080
It really might be their dog.

255
00:11:31,240 --> 00:11:32,240
This guy's trouble.

256
00:11:32,480 --> 00:11:33,320
I'd say

257
00:11:33,380 --> 00:11:34,240
he's the thief.

258
00:11:34,280 --> 00:11:35,170
What did you say?

259
00:11:35,210 --> 00:11:36,080
You with them or what?

260
00:11:36,080 --> 00:11:36,990
Here to stir things up.

261
00:11:37,480 --> 00:11:38,320
Let go or not?

262
00:11:38,410 --> 00:11:39,480
Let go, or I won't be nice.

263
00:11:39,480 --> 00:11:40,510
Stop watching.

264
00:11:40,510 --> 00:11:41,480
We got jobs to do.

265
00:11:41,660 --> 00:11:43,630
The dog's been kept at her nail salon
for a while.

266
00:11:43,630 --> 00:11:45,210
Anyone who's been there's seen it, right?

267
00:11:45,240 --> 00:11:46,510
- Yeah.
- Cut the chatter.

268
00:11:46,630 --> 00:11:48,240
Let go or I'll get rough!

269
00:11:49,510 --> 00:11:50,790
Don't lay hands on girls.

270
00:11:50,950 --> 00:11:52,460
You're a grown man, what are you doing?

271
00:11:52,510 --> 00:11:53,600
What's it to you?

272
00:11:53,810 --> 00:11:54,880
Who do you think you are?

273
00:11:55,550 --> 00:11:56,720
Not letting go? Fine!

274
00:11:56,720 --> 00:11:57,560
Stop!

275
00:11:59,070 --> 00:11:59,970
What's going on here?

276
00:12:00,000 --> 00:12:01,030
And who are you?

277
00:12:01,550 --> 00:12:02,510
Who are you?

278
00:12:03,550 --> 00:12:04,440
Officer!

279
00:12:04,480 --> 00:12:05,520
They cause trouble,

280
00:12:05,570 --> 00:12:06,560
trying to snatch my dog.

281
00:12:06,600 --> 00:12:07,650
Is that so?

282
00:12:07,730 --> 00:12:08,850
- Yes.
- Move along, people.

283
00:12:08,870 --> 00:12:10,330
- I sell dogs here.
- Move along.

284
00:12:16,510 --> 00:12:17,350
Officer,

285
00:12:17,600 --> 00:12:18,790
this man is a dog thief.

286
00:12:18,910 --> 00:12:20,320
He stole her dog,

287
00:12:20,320 --> 00:12:21,530
picked on her for being mute,

288
00:12:21,560 --> 00:12:22,270
and slandered her.

289
00:12:22,390 --> 00:12:23,240
Who's slandering who?

290
00:12:23,240 --> 00:12:24,440
You're the one slandering me!

291
00:12:24,630 --> 00:12:25,870
All dogs can look alike.

292
00:12:26,150 --> 00:12:27,150
What proof do you have

293
00:12:27,150 --> 00:12:28,240
that this is your dog?

294
00:12:28,390 --> 00:12:29,910
You just don't want to pay.

295
00:12:30,390 --> 00:12:31,480
Easy, easy.

296
00:12:31,520 --> 00:12:32,460
Don't be unreasonable.

297
00:12:37,750 --> 00:12:38,590
Look.

298
00:12:39,630 --> 00:12:40,580
The markings.

299
00:12:40,600 --> 00:12:41,630
The white fur on its head.

300
00:12:41,630 --> 00:12:42,870
They match exactly.

301
00:12:50,270 --> 00:12:51,110
Care to explain?

302
00:12:55,030 --> 00:12:55,910
I... I...

303
00:12:56,200 --> 00:12:57,040
I really don't know.

304
00:12:58,630 --> 00:13:00,000
Officer, this dog was left with me

305
00:13:00,000 --> 00:13:01,000
by someone to sell.

306
00:13:01,260 --> 00:13:02,830
After it sold, we'd split the profits.

307
00:13:02,880 --> 00:13:04,440
I haven't sold it yet, alright?

308
00:13:04,440 --> 00:13:05,340
I haven't made a dime.

309
00:13:05,510 --> 00:13:06,440
Who gave it to you?

310
00:13:07,150 --> 00:13:08,080
Listen up.

311
00:13:08,300 --> 00:13:09,960
It's under serious investigation right now.

312
00:13:10,240 --> 00:13:11,630
If you don't want trouble,

313
00:13:11,870 --> 00:13:13,080
you'd better cooperate.

314
00:13:13,390 --> 00:13:14,320
Of course. I will.

315
00:13:14,510 --> 00:13:15,350
I'll cooperate.

316
00:13:17,440 --> 00:13:18,440
It's his dog.

317
00:13:18,440 --> 00:13:19,430
I'm not involved.

318
00:13:19,450 --> 00:13:20,480
I'm just the seller.

319
00:13:22,330 --> 00:13:24,480
This could be the gang we're after.

320
00:13:26,770 --> 00:13:28,270
Call him. Tell him to come over now.

321
00:13:40,790 --> 00:13:41,870
It's sold already?

322
00:13:46,680 --> 00:13:47,550
Yeah, that's him.

323
00:13:47,570 --> 00:13:48,970
Officer, he took the dog.

324
00:13:49,000 --> 00:13:49,840
Stop it.

325
00:13:51,390 --> 00:13:52,480
That hurts.

326
00:13:53,480 --> 00:13:54,320
Why are you running?

327
00:13:55,510 --> 00:13:56,350
Why are you running?

328
00:13:57,440 --> 00:13:59,030
She says he's her neighbor.

329
00:14:00,460 --> 00:14:01,390
You know sign language?

330
00:14:01,790 --> 00:14:02,630
Just a little.

331
00:14:03,910 --> 00:14:04,840
Did you steal the dog?

332
00:14:05,000 --> 00:14:05,840
Yes.

333
00:14:06,000 --> 00:14:06,840
No, I...

334
00:14:06,960 --> 00:14:07,880
Did you or didn't you?

335
00:14:08,320 --> 00:14:09,870
Yes, I caught it.

336
00:14:10,870 --> 00:14:11,750
That's enough.

337
00:14:11,810 --> 00:14:12,670
Come with us.

338
00:14:12,670 --> 00:14:13,840
No, wait, officer.

339
00:14:14,150 --> 00:14:15,510
This dog chased me

340
00:14:15,720 --> 00:14:16,600
and tried to bite me.

341
00:14:16,790 --> 00:14:18,030
I had no choice but to catch it.

342
00:14:18,510 --> 00:14:19,750
Don't be fooled by its size.

343
00:14:19,990 --> 00:14:20,800
It's very protective.

344
00:14:20,820 --> 00:14:21,840
It won't let go.

345
00:14:21,840 --> 00:14:22,680
I really got bitten.

346
00:14:22,910 --> 00:14:23,750
Really bitten.

347
00:14:25,150 --> 00:14:26,240
Alright, that's clear.

348
00:14:26,690 --> 00:14:27,940
Give him to the patrol officers.

349
00:14:28,150 --> 00:14:28,990
We should take him.

350
00:14:29,070 --> 00:14:30,510
Could be tied to the Dog Theft Case.

351
00:14:30,670 --> 00:14:31,510
That's not necessary.

352
00:14:31,860 --> 00:14:32,720
No need for that.

353
00:14:32,720 --> 00:14:34,120
Why so much talking?

354
00:14:36,080 --> 00:14:36,920
You're coming too.

355
00:14:37,080 --> 00:14:37,920
Move.

356
00:14:39,200 --> 00:14:40,040
Easy, go easy.

357
00:14:51,360 --> 00:14:52,200
Officer.

358
00:14:58,240 --> 00:14:59,390
It means thank you.

359
00:14:59,630 --> 00:15:01,080
The nail salon girl asked me

360
00:15:01,080 --> 00:15:02,080
to pass it on to you.

361
00:15:02,150 --> 00:15:04,390
It's fine. It's the right thing to do.

362
00:15:05,080 --> 00:15:07,510
Are you investigating that Dog Thief Case?

363
00:15:11,960 --> 00:15:12,960
You just got back, right?

364
00:15:13,360 --> 00:15:14,390
You've heard about it too?

365
00:15:14,910 --> 00:15:17,030
I heard when I called home.

366
00:15:17,440 --> 00:15:19,440
It happened near where I live.

367
00:15:19,660 --> 00:15:20,940
I know that neighborhood well.

368
00:15:21,720 --> 00:15:22,560
Why don't you

369
00:15:22,750 --> 00:15:23,790
leave your number?

370
00:15:24,000 --> 00:15:25,390
If anything comes up, I'll call you.

371
00:15:25,750 --> 00:15:27,480
Just a way to thank you.

372
00:15:34,940 --> 00:15:36,500
(New contact)

373
00:15:37,240 --> 00:15:38,080
I'm Wang Yimo.

374
00:15:38,630 --> 00:15:39,470
Tang Tang.

375
00:15:48,740 --> 00:15:51,140
(Mobile)

376
00:15:58,390 --> 00:15:59,230
Morning, Mr. Wang.

377
00:16:01,510 --> 00:16:02,350
Morning, boss.

378
00:16:04,900 --> 00:16:06,060
(Hongyun Restaurant)

379
00:16:15,260 --> 00:16:19,380
(Welcome to Hongyun Restaurant)

380
00:16:19,380 --> 00:16:21,380
(Hongyun Restaurant)

381
00:16:21,390 --> 00:16:22,230
Qiang?

382
00:16:22,750 --> 00:16:23,590
Qiang?

383
00:16:54,960 --> 00:16:55,800
Dad.

384
00:16:58,480 --> 00:16:59,320
Yimo.

385
00:17:05,110 --> 00:17:05,950
I'm back.

386
00:17:25,480 --> 00:17:26,320
Dad.

387
00:17:42,070 --> 00:17:43,510
How long are you staying this time?

388
00:17:44,260 --> 00:17:45,490
How did you get time off work?

389
00:17:46,200 --> 00:17:47,040
Dad,

390
00:17:47,680 --> 00:17:49,090
I plan to stay here in our hometown.

391
00:17:49,480 --> 00:17:50,320
Not going back.

392
00:17:52,680 --> 00:17:53,520
Not going back?

393
00:17:56,400 --> 00:17:57,240
What are you doing?

394
00:18:01,880 --> 00:18:02,880
Sounds like

395
00:18:03,240 --> 00:18:05,510
Yimo is staying this time.

396
00:18:07,510 --> 00:18:08,480
She's staying?

397
00:18:09,700 --> 00:18:10,540
Really?

398
00:18:10,550 --> 00:18:11,390
Seems like it.

399
00:18:13,920 --> 00:18:14,760
Don't go.

400
00:18:16,160 --> 00:18:17,960
Something feels off in here.

401
00:18:20,550 --> 00:18:21,550
Tell me the truth.

402
00:18:22,270 --> 00:18:24,240
Did you get laid off?

403
00:18:24,590 --> 00:18:25,430
No.

404
00:18:25,750 --> 00:18:26,680
I'm doing great at work.

405
00:18:27,680 --> 00:18:29,270
I just want to be closer to you.

406
00:18:29,830 --> 00:18:31,480
I don't want to be that far away anymore.

407
00:18:31,640 --> 00:18:33,400
Isn't it nice for us to stay together?

408
00:18:33,830 --> 00:18:35,440
Xinjing is such a great place.

409
00:18:36,110 --> 00:18:37,270
You were doing so well there.

410
00:18:37,960 --> 00:18:39,110
Why come back here?

411
00:18:39,240 --> 00:18:40,830
Did you forget what you promised me?

412
00:18:41,480 --> 00:18:42,880
I'd get settled in a big city,

413
00:18:43,050 --> 00:18:44,970
then you'd transfer the place
and come find me.

414
00:18:45,200 --> 00:18:46,690
So why are you backing out now?

415
00:18:46,710 --> 00:18:47,800
You keep changing your mind.

416
00:18:48,680 --> 00:18:49,750
Transfer the restaurant

417
00:18:50,000 --> 00:18:51,310
is not easy at all.

418
00:18:54,920 --> 00:18:55,760
Dad,

419
00:18:56,160 --> 00:18:57,070
tell me the truth.

420
00:18:57,640 --> 00:18:58,830
Who exactly are you

421
00:18:59,590 --> 00:19:00,430
staying for?

422
00:19:02,850 --> 00:19:03,830
Who else could it be for?

423
00:19:04,790 --> 00:19:06,720
It's for the regulars downstairs.

424
00:19:07,440 --> 00:19:08,880
They've been eating here for decades.

425
00:19:08,880 --> 00:19:09,730
They're like family.

426
00:19:09,730 --> 00:19:10,720
I can't bear to leave.

427
00:19:11,790 --> 00:19:12,680
They're family?

428
00:19:12,680 --> 00:19:13,830
Then what am I?

429
00:19:17,000 --> 00:19:18,750
You graduated from such a great school.

430
00:19:19,400 --> 00:19:20,920
You have a bright future ahead of you.

431
00:19:21,610 --> 00:19:22,980
You can't stay here forever.

432
00:19:23,310 --> 00:19:24,150
Dad.

433
00:19:25,920 --> 00:19:26,760
Ali.

434
00:19:27,750 --> 00:19:28,590
Come in.

435
00:19:31,110 --> 00:19:31,950
Yimo?

436
00:19:32,480 --> 00:19:33,320
Ms. Tong?

437
00:19:34,240 --> 00:19:35,270
You're back.

438
00:19:37,310 --> 00:19:38,550
Ms. Tong, look at my dad.

439
00:19:38,840 --> 00:19:40,820
I just got back
and he's telling me to leave.

440
00:19:41,750 --> 00:19:42,590
Ali.

441
00:19:42,880 --> 00:19:43,720
Come on.

442
00:19:43,960 --> 00:19:46,070
You're always talking about Yimo,

443
00:19:46,270 --> 00:19:47,590
saying how much you miss her.

444
00:19:48,030 --> 00:19:49,070
Now she's back,

445
00:19:49,340 --> 00:19:50,780
why are you pushing her to leave?

446
00:19:51,000 --> 00:19:52,160
You don't understand.

447
00:19:53,840 --> 00:19:55,210
I'm doing this for her own good.

448
00:19:57,240 --> 00:19:58,080
Dad,

449
00:19:58,440 --> 00:19:59,590
I know what's good for me.

450
00:20:02,110 --> 00:20:02,990
Captain Zhao.

451
00:20:03,030 --> 00:20:03,870
Hey, Wen.

452
00:20:04,220 --> 00:20:05,680
Captain Zhao, I was looking for you.

453
00:20:05,880 --> 00:20:07,140
The autopsy report is out.

454
00:20:08,690 --> 00:20:09,450
After examination,

455
00:20:09,500 --> 00:20:11,130
Liu Yan's time of death was 5 days ago.

456
00:20:11,240 --> 00:20:12,200
(Forensic Autopsy Report)
Cause of death was poisoning.

457
00:20:12,460 --> 00:20:13,790
The toxin in her stomach

458
00:20:13,790 --> 00:20:15,550
matches what was found in the sausage.

459
00:20:15,880 --> 00:20:16,540
It's confirmed

460
00:20:16,610 --> 00:20:18,100
the poison was added to the sausage.

461
00:20:18,270 --> 00:20:19,810
The same as the serial dog-theft cases.

462
00:20:20,030 --> 00:20:21,400
And one more thing.

463
00:20:21,550 --> 00:20:23,270
No signs of forced ingestion.

464
00:20:23,440 --> 00:20:24,880
Looks like she ate it willingly.

465
00:20:25,270 --> 00:20:26,160
Willingly?

466
00:20:27,340 --> 00:20:28,440
Accidental ingestion?

467
00:20:29,000 --> 00:20:30,270
That would make it an accident.

468
00:20:30,720 --> 00:20:31,570
Hold on.

469
00:20:31,590 --> 00:20:33,030
Why was the dosage so high this time?

470
00:20:33,400 --> 00:20:34,830
The dosage was indeed

471
00:20:35,200 --> 00:20:36,440
four times higher, actually.

472
00:20:36,750 --> 00:20:39,030
Far beyond the lethal dose for an adult.

473
00:20:40,830 --> 00:20:42,480
I only did it once.

474
00:20:43,160 --> 00:20:44,440
I didn't steal any other dogs.

475
00:20:45,510 --> 00:20:46,350
How did you steal it?

476
00:20:46,790 --> 00:20:47,670
Did you poison it?

477
00:20:47,790 --> 00:20:48,630
No, no.

478
00:20:49,070 --> 00:20:51,000
I just used a net

479
00:20:51,550 --> 00:20:52,390
and snagged it.

480
00:20:53,910 --> 00:20:54,910
I didn't poison anything.

481
00:20:55,200 --> 00:20:56,040
You can test it.

482
00:20:57,630 --> 00:20:58,720
Why did you steal the dog?

483
00:21:00,310 --> 00:21:01,750
Stop stalling and just talk.

484
00:21:02,160 --> 00:21:03,830
I run the laundry shop next door.

485
00:21:04,350 --> 00:21:06,310
I thought she was pretty

486
00:21:06,830 --> 00:21:08,200
and wanted to date her.

487
00:21:08,510 --> 00:21:09,510
But her dog...

488
00:21:09,650 --> 00:21:11,680
Whenever it saw me, it came at me,
trying to bite.

489
00:21:12,270 --> 00:21:13,920
I couldn't take it anymore, so I...

490
00:21:14,720 --> 00:21:15,680
She wouldn't date you,

491
00:21:15,680 --> 00:21:16,590
so you stole her dog?

492
00:21:17,720 --> 00:21:19,000
You went into her shop.

493
00:21:19,350 --> 00:21:20,590
Why would the dog bite you?

494
00:21:21,030 --> 00:21:24,160
I thought she was pretty before,

495
00:21:24,880 --> 00:21:26,830
so I touched her once.

496
00:21:27,510 --> 00:21:29,880
Didn't expect the dog to hold such a grudge.

497
00:21:29,880 --> 00:21:30,920
It's so protective of her.

498
00:21:31,070 --> 00:21:32,200
Don't be fooled by its size.

499
00:21:32,460 --> 00:21:34,070
It bit me bad. Took three stitches.

500
00:21:34,240 --> 00:21:35,830
I just wanted to get rid of the dog

501
00:21:36,430 --> 00:21:37,550
so it wouldn't be in my way.

502
00:21:43,500 --> 00:21:44,540
(Suspect Profile)

503
00:21:44,540 --> 00:21:46,140
(Interrogation Record)

504
00:21:52,440 --> 00:21:53,280
What's going on?

505
00:21:54,050 --> 00:21:55,600
Is he the suspect you're looking for?

506
00:21:58,240 --> 00:21:59,110
I told you.

507
00:21:59,250 --> 00:22:00,340
No need to bring him back.

508
00:22:00,750 --> 00:22:01,590
Next one.

509
00:22:01,870 --> 00:22:03,670
The next one I catch will be the right one.

510
00:22:06,920 --> 00:22:07,770
Master.

511
00:22:07,790 --> 00:22:09,640
No victim details yet?

512
00:22:10,310 --> 00:22:11,150
Not yet.

513
00:22:13,550 --> 00:22:16,030
I came up with something today.

514
00:22:16,350 --> 00:22:17,400
Let me run it by you.

515
00:22:17,580 --> 00:22:18,420
Look.

516
00:22:18,440 --> 00:22:20,030
All the dog-theft cases

517
00:22:20,350 --> 00:22:21,400
happened in this area.

518
00:22:21,750 --> 00:22:23,790
None of them involve Liu Yan's neighborhood.

519
00:22:24,510 --> 00:22:26,590
And we found out

520
00:22:27,070 --> 00:22:29,350
Liu Yan recently had some money.

521
00:22:29,510 --> 00:22:30,790
She even stopped buying veggies.

522
00:22:31,440 --> 00:22:33,720
There's no reason she'd pick up a sausage.

523
00:22:35,070 --> 00:22:38,030
I don't think Liu Yan ate it by accident.

524
00:22:38,510 --> 00:22:39,640
It feels more like

525
00:22:40,270 --> 00:22:43,480
a poisoning case disguised
as the dog thief's method.

526
00:22:44,400 --> 00:22:46,110
Drop Liu Yan's case.

527
00:22:46,950 --> 00:22:48,950
Stick with the leads
on the serial dog-theft case.

528
00:22:49,510 --> 00:22:52,070
We need to catch the dog thief fast.

529
00:22:52,550 --> 00:22:53,390
That's the priority.

530
00:22:54,400 --> 00:22:55,240
Captain,

531
00:22:55,400 --> 00:22:56,790
I'm taking on both tasks.

532
00:22:56,960 --> 00:22:58,330
I can handle them both, Master.

533
00:22:58,400 --> 00:22:59,640
I won't let Feng from Team One

534
00:22:59,640 --> 00:23:00,750
keep rubbing it in my face.

535
00:23:00,750 --> 00:23:01,720
Alright.

536
00:23:02,210 --> 00:23:03,330
You've been working all day.

537
00:23:03,480 --> 00:23:04,320
Get some rest.

538
00:23:04,440 --> 00:23:05,500
I'm not tired, Master.

539
00:23:05,530 --> 00:23:06,910
You might not be tired, but I am.

540
00:23:07,720 --> 00:23:08,750
I'm not young anymore.

541
00:23:09,000 --> 00:23:10,480
Not like you, full of energy.

542
00:23:11,000 --> 00:23:11,920
We'll talk tomorrow.

543
00:23:14,000 --> 00:23:14,840
Okay, Master.

544
00:23:15,400 --> 00:23:16,830
Take care, Master.

545
00:23:16,830 --> 00:23:18,510
You've worked hard, Master.

546
00:23:19,830 --> 00:23:20,720
That stubborn old man.

547
00:23:21,590 --> 00:23:22,550
Lazy and stubborn.

548
00:23:27,350 --> 00:23:31,310
♪Blue-faced Dou Erdun steals a royal horse♪

549
00:23:31,830 --> 00:23:32,670
♪Red-faced...♪

550
00:23:35,680 --> 00:23:37,310
Tang Tang, what are you doing?

551
00:23:37,590 --> 00:23:39,480
I need a small favor from you.

552
00:23:40,750 --> 00:23:41,960
I've already clocked out.

553
00:23:44,680 --> 00:23:46,440
Just a minute. One minute.

554
00:23:48,110 --> 00:23:49,680
You might not be in a hurry, but I am.

555
00:23:50,610 --> 00:23:52,240
I've been working overtime for two days

556
00:23:52,810 --> 00:23:54,080
to finish this case file.

557
00:23:55,240 --> 00:23:56,110
Besides,

558
00:23:56,220 --> 00:23:57,560
my wife is waiting for me at home

559
00:23:57,590 --> 00:23:59,640
to have noodles with gravy.

560
00:24:00,440 --> 00:24:01,640
Hey, what are you doing?

561
00:24:01,720 --> 00:24:03,350
Noodles won't lump up that fast.

562
00:24:03,440 --> 00:24:05,200
I'll treat you next time, okay?

563
00:24:05,830 --> 00:24:06,670
Please.

564
00:24:07,140 --> 00:24:08,140
Please come in, Mr. Qin.

565
00:24:12,960 --> 00:24:14,000
Liu Yan.

566
00:24:15,720 --> 00:24:18,030
That name's pretty common.

567
00:24:18,030 --> 00:24:19,680
Why come to me to check her?

568
00:24:20,310 --> 00:24:21,720
Her neighbor said she did some time.

569
00:24:22,270 --> 00:24:24,790
I thought if she'd been poisoned,

570
00:24:25,180 --> 00:24:26,480
I'd need to confirm her identity.

571
00:24:53,720 --> 00:24:56,270
I almost got the Nude Banquet Case today.

572
00:24:57,680 --> 00:24:58,680
I know.

573
00:24:59,240 --> 00:25:01,350
Didn't you say in the meeting

574
00:25:01,350 --> 00:25:02,510
you'd make a pledge?

575
00:25:03,160 --> 00:25:04,830
If my Master hadn't stopped me,

576
00:25:05,030 --> 00:25:06,960
I would've gotten the case.

577
00:25:12,640 --> 00:25:15,240
The three obstacles the Chief mentioned today

578
00:25:16,030 --> 00:25:17,070
were really something.

579
00:25:18,350 --> 00:25:19,190
But, Mr. Qin,

580
00:25:20,270 --> 00:25:22,920
you're experienced

581
00:25:23,230 --> 00:25:24,330
and you know the background.

582
00:25:24,720 --> 00:25:25,990
Could you tell me more about it?

583
00:25:28,310 --> 00:25:29,150
Alright.

584
00:25:32,350 --> 00:25:33,590
That case

585
00:25:34,310 --> 00:25:35,480
really was eerie.

586
00:25:36,110 --> 00:25:38,480
At first, things went incredibly smooth.

587
00:25:38,830 --> 00:25:40,400
The businessmen involved

588
00:25:40,480 --> 00:25:42,270
were all caught without much effort.

589
00:25:43,070 --> 00:25:44,790
But here's the strange part.

590
00:25:44,880 --> 00:25:46,750
None of them knew

591
00:25:47,030 --> 00:25:49,480
where the banquet was actually held.

592
00:25:50,400 --> 00:25:52,000
As these businessmen got arrested,

593
00:25:52,000 --> 00:25:53,790
the welfare home staff

594
00:25:53,790 --> 00:25:55,720
who lured minors into the nude banquet

595
00:25:55,720 --> 00:25:57,000
were quickly exposed.

596
00:25:57,400 --> 00:25:59,270
And from the confession

597
00:25:59,270 --> 00:26:00,750
of a welfare home contact we detained,

598
00:26:01,640 --> 00:26:04,200
the key figure in the case

599
00:26:04,350 --> 00:26:05,880
was Bai Qiming.

600
00:26:07,270 --> 00:26:08,740
He single-handedly organized

601
00:26:08,760 --> 00:26:09,890
and ran the entire operation.

602
00:26:10,000 --> 00:26:11,030
After his death,

603
00:26:11,400 --> 00:26:13,830
several key leads were cut off.

604
00:26:15,000 --> 00:26:16,590
Everyone else involved

605
00:26:16,590 --> 00:26:19,110
had unknown identities

606
00:26:19,190 --> 00:26:20,350
and vanished without a trace.

607
00:26:20,590 --> 00:26:22,550
The case dragged on without progress.

608
00:26:23,160 --> 00:26:25,070
It really wore your master down.

609
00:26:26,920 --> 00:26:28,270
After the case hit a dead end,

610
00:26:28,640 --> 00:26:31,000
your master lost a lot of spirit.

611
00:26:31,500 --> 00:26:32,960
His hair even started turning gray.

612
00:26:34,070 --> 00:26:35,160
So that's why

613
00:26:37,030 --> 00:26:39,240
he became disheartened back then.

614
00:26:39,720 --> 00:26:40,960
You think your master

615
00:26:40,960 --> 00:26:42,790
has always been the way he is now?

616
00:26:43,790 --> 00:26:44,750
He's a detective

617
00:26:44,850 --> 00:26:45,990
who's worked his whole life

618
00:26:46,960 --> 00:26:48,590
and weathered plenty of storms.

619
00:26:49,350 --> 00:26:51,270
He used to be full of ambition too.

620
00:26:51,830 --> 00:26:54,440
He had just as much swagger as you do now.

621
00:27:03,550 --> 00:27:04,390
I remember something.

622
00:27:05,350 --> 00:27:07,350
In the Nude Banquet Case,

623
00:27:07,720 --> 00:27:10,400
the social worker who trafficked minors
out of the welfare home

624
00:27:10,780 --> 00:27:11,630
was called Liu Yan.

625
00:27:11,750 --> 00:27:12,590
Hold on.

626
00:27:15,110 --> 00:27:15,950
Here it is.

627
00:27:21,510 --> 00:27:22,480
This is her.

628
00:27:23,300 --> 00:27:24,580
(Suspect Profile: Liu Yan)

629
00:27:24,580 --> 00:27:26,740
(Interrogation Record: Liu Yan)

630
00:27:40,200 --> 00:27:41,640
Ms. Tong, get some rest.

631
00:27:42,110 --> 00:27:43,750
You too. You've had a long trip.

632
00:27:50,110 --> 00:27:51,030
As her father,

633
00:27:51,400 --> 00:27:52,750
talk to her nicely.

634
00:27:52,880 --> 00:27:53,830
Don't be cranky.

635
00:28:02,070 --> 00:28:02,910
Dad,

636
00:28:04,510 --> 00:28:05,640
still mad at me?

637
00:28:06,790 --> 00:28:08,640
Planning to never speak to me again?

638
00:28:13,110 --> 00:28:14,510
Why don't you understand

639
00:28:14,510 --> 00:28:15,960
I'm doing this for your own good?

640
00:28:16,960 --> 00:28:18,310
You don't understand me, either.

641
00:28:20,880 --> 00:28:23,070
Why didn't you tell me you were coming back?

642
00:28:24,310 --> 00:28:25,550
Why come back all of a sudden?

643
00:28:27,680 --> 00:28:29,270
Life in the big city is exhausting.

644
00:28:31,330 --> 00:28:32,920
I've been living out there all by myself.

645
00:28:33,920 --> 00:28:35,270
If I get sick,

646
00:28:36,010 --> 00:28:37,560
even just a small headache or fever,

647
00:28:37,830 --> 00:28:39,400
there's no one to look after me.

648
00:28:40,270 --> 00:28:41,640
No one like you,

649
00:28:42,440 --> 00:28:43,350
making me soup,

650
00:28:43,880 --> 00:28:45,030
boiling pear tea for me.

651
00:28:46,720 --> 00:28:48,350
There's no place as warm as home.

652
00:28:52,030 --> 00:28:54,110
You think life out there's been easy for me?

653
00:28:55,590 --> 00:28:56,880
Dad, you have no idea

654
00:28:57,590 --> 00:29:00,000
how exclusionary my company is.

655
00:29:01,350 --> 00:29:03,200
Just because I'm from a small town,

656
00:29:03,680 --> 00:29:05,480
they all look down on me.

657
00:29:11,550 --> 00:29:12,390
Lately,

658
00:29:14,000 --> 00:29:15,550
I've been having nightmares again.

659
00:29:22,790 --> 00:29:23,680
Dad,

660
00:29:25,830 --> 00:29:27,640
I never had the courage to tell you before.

661
00:29:28,720 --> 00:29:30,000
But now I'm back.

662
00:29:31,000 --> 00:29:32,640
Are you still going to send me away?

663
00:29:44,880 --> 00:29:45,830
Since you're back,

664
00:29:47,610 --> 00:29:48,640
stay for a few more days.

665
00:29:51,190 --> 00:29:52,510
We'll figure it out later.

666
00:29:53,550 --> 00:29:54,750
I'm here for you.

667
00:29:56,030 --> 00:29:57,790
You'll never have nightmares again.

668
00:30:28,860 --> 00:30:29,900
(Certificate of Honor: Gold Prize)

669
00:30:37,060 --> 00:30:39,540
(4th Ambadi International Piano Competition;
Wang Yimo)

670
00:31:12,380 --> 00:31:15,100
(Qingcheng Public Security Bureau)

671
00:31:55,500 --> 00:31:57,620
(Suspect Profile: Liu Yan)

672
00:32:00,420 --> 00:32:01,460
(Forensic Autopsy Report)

673
00:32:01,480 --> 00:32:03,550
(Crime Scene Notes; Case Registration Form)
The case dragged on without progress.

674
00:32:04,030 --> 00:32:06,070
It really wore your mentor out.

675
00:32:07,680 --> 00:32:09,750
In the Nude Banquet Case,

676
00:32:10,030 --> 00:32:12,750
the social worker who trafficked minors
out of the welfare home

677
00:32:13,200 --> 00:32:14,040
was called Liu Yan.

678
00:32:14,040 --> 00:32:16,060
(Suspect Profile: Liu Yan)

679
00:32:23,590 --> 00:32:24,430
Yimo,

680
00:32:25,720 --> 00:32:26,560
what are you doing?

681
00:32:27,440 --> 00:32:28,280
Dad,

682
00:32:28,300 --> 00:32:29,180
I've told you before.

683
00:32:29,180 --> 00:32:30,790
The house is too cluttered.

684
00:32:30,880 --> 00:32:31,750
You never tidy up.

685
00:32:33,550 --> 00:32:34,480
Looks fine to me.

686
00:32:38,400 --> 00:32:39,240
Alright.

687
00:32:39,480 --> 00:32:41,240
Whatever my daughter says goes.

688
00:32:43,920 --> 00:32:44,760
What's this?

689
00:32:45,880 --> 00:32:48,160
Class of 1990.

690
00:32:48,160 --> 00:32:50,030
Huaxin Middle School, Qingcheng.

691
00:32:50,850 --> 00:32:52,240
It's your graduation picture, right?

692
00:32:54,220 --> 00:32:56,240
If you hadn't found it, I'd have forgotten.

693
00:32:56,350 --> 00:32:57,550
Which one is you?

694
00:32:58,160 --> 00:32:59,070
Look closely.

695
00:32:59,750 --> 00:33:01,510
This one, right?

696
00:33:03,200 --> 00:33:04,070
Sharp eyes.

697
00:33:05,920 --> 00:33:06,790
And who's this?

698
00:33:10,260 --> 00:33:12,860
(Class of 1990,
Huaxin Middle School, Qingcheng)

699
00:33:14,270 --> 00:33:15,110
I really

700
00:33:15,510 --> 00:33:17,270
can't remember his name.

701
00:33:17,720 --> 00:33:20,240
He looks kinda familiar though.

702
00:33:23,640 --> 00:33:24,480
I'll get the door.

703
00:33:29,920 --> 00:33:30,760
Ms. Tong.

704
00:33:31,240 --> 00:33:32,080
Yimo.

705
00:33:32,640 --> 00:33:33,640
I just baked bread.

706
00:33:33,880 --> 00:33:35,440
Brought some over for you and your dad.

707
00:33:35,640 --> 00:33:36,590
Thanks, Ms. Tong.

708
00:33:36,880 --> 00:33:37,720
Don't mention it.

709
00:33:38,110 --> 00:33:39,590
Look what I found.

710
00:33:39,920 --> 00:33:40,760
What's this?

711
00:33:40,950 --> 00:33:42,490
My dad's middle school graduation photo.

712
00:33:44,310 --> 00:33:45,350
Handsome, right?

713
00:34:00,070 --> 00:34:05,560
♪Dreams of the past sleep in the chill♪

714
00:34:05,560 --> 00:34:09,010
♪Now I run toward the light♪

715
00:34:10,860 --> 00:34:16,120
♪What does the fire burn,
what does it reveal?♪

716
00:34:16,440 --> 00:34:20,090
♪Is the answer found when the sun rises♪

717
00:34:20,700 --> 00:34:24,990
♪If it's all a lie♪

718
00:34:26,180 --> 00:34:30,350
♪Should I tear it open?♪

719
00:34:31,680 --> 00:34:36,400
♪If it's all part of the journey♪

720
00:34:37,080 --> 00:34:41,930
♪Then face the blaze head-on♪

721
00:34:42,320 --> 00:34:46,790
♪Let the sun awaken my heart's crave♪

722
00:34:47,330 --> 00:34:53,060
♪Pain reminds me I'm alive♪

723
00:34:53,180 --> 00:34:57,990
♪The world can't take away every clear sky♪

724
00:34:58,640 --> 00:35:03,790
♪The hotter it gets, the fiercer I fight♪

725
00:35:04,100 --> 00:35:08,820
♪Let the sun burn away all I lean upon♪

726
00:35:09,160 --> 00:35:14,820
♪Leave me only what endures♪

727
00:35:14,930 --> 00:35:20,480
♪At the cliff's edge, all fear shatters♪

728
00:35:20,540 --> 00:35:27,490
♪With a grounded heart, a soul like fire♪
